                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-defend2258" type="age" value="30"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18320405-268-off1570" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-off1570" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-off1570" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing on the <rs id="t18320405-268-cd1571" type="crimeDate">1st of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-268-off1570 t18320405-268-cd1571"></join>, 2 sovereigns and 6 half-crowns, the monies of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18320405-268-victim2260" type="victimName">
                           William 
                           German
                        <interp inst="t18320405-268-victim2260" type="surname" value="German"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18320405-268-victim2260" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18320405-268-victim2260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-268-off1570 t18320405-268-victim2260"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2261">
                  WILLIAM 
                  GERMAN
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2261" type="surname" value="GERMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2261" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am <rs id="t18320405-268-viclabel1572" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-268-victim2260 t18320405-268-viclabel1572"></join> to Mr. Ranson, a baker, in the Minories. On the 1st of April, between seven and eight o'clock, I went into a public-house at the corner of <placeName id="t18320405-268-crimeloc1573">Crispin-street, Spitalfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-268-crimeloc1573" type="placeName" value="Crispin-street, Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-268-crimeloc1573" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-268-off1570 t18320405-268-crimeloc1573"></join>, and had in my left-hand waistcoat pocket two sovereigns and six half-crowns- I was sitting in a box with my head on the table, and fell asleep; I was not intoxicated - the prisoner, who I have known four years, went with me to the house; he was standing up when I fell asleep; he was close to the fire, not within reach of my pocket - I was awoke, and directly missed my money; he was then gone; I saw him in custody in about twenty minutes - he said he had got plenty of money, and produced two sovereigns, three half-crowns, a penny and a farthing, which he said were his own, and he could produce 10l. if it was wanted - he told me that morning that he had no money - he borrowed 6d. of me, and gave a duplicate as security for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2262">
                  JOHN 
                  MADGE
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2262" type="surname" value="MADGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2262" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a baker, and live in Petticoat-lane - I know the prosecutor and prisoner. I saw them both at the public-house; I went in after them; the prosecutor laid asleep, with his head on the table - the prisoner was standing by the fire, smoking his pipe, about two or three feet from German; nobody else was in the room; I did not see the prisoner do any thing - he left three or four minutes after I came in; we both left together - I returned directly, having heard something at the bar, and awoke the prosecutor, who complained of losing his money in about five minutes - the prisoner was out of work then, and had been so for some time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2263">
                  HANNAH 
                  HARNETT
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2263" type="surname" value="HARNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2263" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2263" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant at the public-house. The prosecutor and prisoner came in together; there was nobody else in the room; the prosecutor would not take any thing, but laid his head on the table, and went to sleep - the prisoner called for a pint of ale, and sat down by him; in about five minutes Madge came in;<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183204050111"></xptr>they both went outside the door; I saw the prisoner put his hand into the prosecutor's left-hand waistcoat pocket twice, and the second time I told master of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2264">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SAVAGE
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2264" type="surname" value="SAVAGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2264" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I took the prisoner in charge; he produced two sovereigns, three half-crowns, a penny, and a halfpenny, and said he could prove where he had changed a sovereign that morning - before I heard of the robbery I saw him running up Red Lion-street; that was at a quarter to eight o'clock; the prosecutor informed me of the robbery - I went and found him.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2265">
                  JOHN 
                  BURROUGH
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2265" type="surname" value="BURROUGH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2265" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I went with Savage, and took the prisoner in charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went into a coffee-shop - the prosecutor came in, and six or seven females in his company; the prosecutor took me to the public-house to have some gin - we had three or four half-pints, and five or six pints of ale; we returned to the coffee-shop, and then went to this house; he fell asleep - I went out, and talked to Madge at the door for two or three minutes; they knew I had money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-268-person2266">
                  JOHN 
                  MADGE
               <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2266" type="surname" value="MADGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2266" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-person2266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have not known him possessed of money lately.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320405-268-verdict1574" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-verdict1574" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30. - <rs id="t18320405-268-punish1575" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320405-268-punish1575" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-268-defend2258 t18320405-268-punish1575"></join>
